sentences: Max Rudolf (June 15, 1902 — February 28, 1995) was a German conductor and music institute teacher.
Max Rudolf (June 15, 1902 — February 28, 1995) was a German conductor and music institute teacher.
In 1929, he became principal conductor of the German Theatre in Prague.
In 1940, Rudolf emigrated to the United States, and took American citizenship in 1945.
